00:32:10,600 --> 00:32:13,800
coming in from the left vertical side of the square.

855
00:32:15,020 --> 00:32:16,880
What about the number going out?

856
00:32:17,980 --> 00:32:18,460
Oh,

857
00:32:18,460 --> 00:32:19,360
there's another factor.

858
00:32:19,880 --> 00:32:20,960
There's another factor.

859
00:32:21,080 --> 00:32:22,180
Anybody know what the other factor is?

860
00:32:23,480 --> 00:32:24,180
Delta y.

861
00:32:24,640 --> 00:32:25,120
Yeah,

862
00:32:25,120 --> 00:32:27,120
the size of the y interval here.

863
00:32:27,480 --> 00:32:27,960
Obviously,

864
00:32:27,960 --> 00:32:30,260
the bigger the y interval for a given velocity,

865
00:32:30,540 --> 00:32:31,840
the more points will enter there.

866
00:32:32,000 --> 00:32:32,940
So there's another factor,

867
00:32:32,940 --> 00:32:33,900
which is just delta y.

868
00:32:37,000 --> 00:32:37,180
Now,

869
00:32:37,180 --> 00:32:38,520
how about the number of

870
00:32:38,520 --> 00:32:39,860
points going out on this side?

871
00:32:42,220 --> 00:32:44,480
That's also proportional to vx,

872
00:32:44,660 --> 00:32:46,620
but vx at the displaced point.

873
00:32:47,640 --> 00:32:48,300
All right,

874
00:32:48,300 --> 00:32:49,700
so we have to move ahead a little bit

875
00:32:49,700 --> 00:32:52,840
and subtract the points coming out on this side,

876
00:32:52,900 --> 00:32:54,080
exactly what we did over here.

877
00:32:54,500 --> 00:32:56,020
The answer is going to be

878
00:32:56,020 --> 00:33:00,040
the derivative of vx with respect to x

879
00:33:03,280 --> 00:33:06,460
times delta y times delta x.

880
00:33:06,460 --> 00:33:07,940
Where does this delta x come from?

881
00:33:10,560 --> 00:33:12,960
The difference of the velocity here and here

882
00:33:13,960 --> 00:33:15,590
is the derivative of v with

883
00:33:15,590 --> 00:33:17,220
respect to x times delta x.

884
00:33:18,140 --> 00:33:18,820
All right?

885
00:33:18,960 --> 00:33:21,660
The difference between the x component of velocity

886
00:33:21,660 --> 00:33:23,460
on the right-hand side of the square

887
00:33:23,460 --> 00:33:25,020
and on the left-hand side of the square

888
00:33:25,900 --> 00:33:28,070
is the derivative of v with

889
00:33:28,070 --> 00:33:30,240
respect to x times delta x.

890
00:33:30,800 --> 00:33:33,040
We have to multiply that by delta y

891
00:33:33,040 --> 00:33:35,620
to find the net number of points

892
00:33:35,620 --> 00:33:38,700
coming into on this side

893
00:33:38,700 --> 00:33:41,080
minus out on this side,

894
00:33:41,220 --> 00:33:42,100
and that's this.

895
00:33:43,720 --> 00:33:44,400
Okay,

896
00:33:44,400 --> 00:33:46,680
so this is the net number of points

897
00:33:46,680 --> 00:33:48,200
coming into the rectangle

898
00:33:48,200 --> 00:33:50,080
through the vertical edges.

899
00:33:50,620 --> 00:33:51,300
Now,

900
00:33:51,300 --> 00:33:52,560
what about the horizontal edges?

901
00:33:53,420 --> 00:33:54,980
The horizontal edges,

902
00:33:54,980 --> 00:33:56,980
things can also move in,

903
00:33:57,120 --> 00:34:00,660
but now the x component of velocity

904
00:34:00,660 --> 00:34:03,880
is not relevant

905
00:34:03,880 --> 00:34:05,520
to particles coming in

906
00:34:05,620 --> 00:34:06,600
in this direction.

907
00:34:06,880 --> 00:34:09,320
Only the y component of the motion

908
00:34:09,320 --> 00:34:12,260
is relevant on the horizontal boundaries.

909
00:34:12,960 --> 00:34:13,520
So,

910
00:34:13,520 --> 00:34:15,699
how many particles come in from the lower end?

911
00:34:16,139 --> 00:34:16,699
Well,

912
00:34:16,699 --> 00:34:17,380
that's going to be

913
00:34:19,379 --> 00:34:20,199
v sub y

914
00:34:22,060 --> 00:34:23,400
at the lower end

915
00:34:23,400 --> 00:34:24,900
times delta x.

916
00:34:28,580 --> 00:34:30,639
But then we have to subtract off

917
00:34:31,560 --> 00:34:34,580
v sub y coming out of the top end here,

918
00:34:38,179 --> 00:34:39,860
in order to find the difference

919
00:34:39,860 --> 00:34:41,560
of the incoming points

920
00:34:41,560 --> 00:34:43,080
and the outgoing points

921
00:34:43,409 --> 00:34:44,739
on the bottom and top.

922
00:34:45,370 --> 00:34:46,534
So that will give us

923
00:34:46,534 --> 00:34:47,699
the derivative of v sub y

924
00:34:47,699 --> 00:34:49,360
with respect to what?

925
00:34:50,300 --> 00:34:51,460
With respect to y,

926
00:34:51,760 --> 00:34:53,159
because we're going from bottom to top,

927
00:34:55,800 --> 00:34:56,840
times delta y.

928
00:35:01,460 --> 00:35:03,400
The whole net change

929
00:35:03,400 --> 00:35:07,300
in the number of points in this rectangle

930
00:35:07,300 --> 00:35:10,660
is simply proportional to delta x delta y,

931
00:35:10,920 --> 00:35:12,960
that's just the area of the little region,

932
00:35:13,120 --> 00:35:15,520
times a quantity which is called

933
00:35:15,520 --> 00:35:18,140
the divergence of the velocity field.

934
00:35:18,920 --> 00:35:20,800
This is the velocity field.

935
00:35:21,100 --> 00:35:23,160
It can vary from place to place,

936
00:35:24,200 --> 00:35:25,980
but it's definite and it's fixed.

937
00:35:26,240 --> 00:35:28,680
And this is the derivative of v sub x

938
00:35:28,680 --> 00:35:29,620
with respect to x

939
00:35:30,380 --> 00:35:32,300
plus the derivative of v sub y

940
00:35:32,300 --> 00:35:33,540
with respect to y.

941
00:35:36,260 --> 00:35:37,520
If this is positive,

942
00:35:37,660 --> 00:35:39,140
it corresponds to a decrease

943
00:35:39,140 --> 00:35:40,320
in the density.

944
00:35:42,960 --> 00:35:44,680
What if it's an incompressible fluid?

945
00:35:45,400 --> 00:35:47,060
If it's an incompressible fluid,

946
00:35:47,280 --> 00:35:49,200
then the net number of points coming in

947
00:35:49,200 --> 00:35:51,100
and going out must add up to zero.

948
00:35:53,440 --> 00:35:56,840
We can forget the delta x times delta y,

949
00:35:57,060 --> 00:35:57,880
that's just a number,

950
00:35:57,980 --> 00:35:59,100
a little area,

951
00:35:59,680 --> 00:36:01,100
and so the condition of

952
00:36:01,100 --> 00:36:02,020
