970
00:36:39,360 --> 00:36:40,780
if the x component of velocity

971
00:36:40,780 --> 00:36:42,520
is increasing in one direction,

972
00:36:42,820 --> 00:36:45,200
then the y component must be decreasing

973
00:36:45,200 --> 00:36:46,240
in the other direction.

974
00:36:47,020 --> 00:36:48,280
So it does not say

975
00:36:48,280 --> 00:36:51,040
that the velocity can't change

976
00:36:51,040 --> 00:36:52,040
from place to place.

977
00:36:52,500 --> 00:36:54,460
It doesn't require the motion

978
00:36:54,460 --> 00:36:55,900
to be just rigid motion.

979
00:36:58,520 --> 00:37:00,540
More complicated kinds of things

